# RUN: tianchenrv-rvv-q4-0-q8-0-shape-selection-test | FileCheck %s

# The N3 capability/resource-aware autotuner for the ggml Q4_0 x Q8_0 block-dot:
# the COMPILER SELECTS the kernel shape, DERIVED from capability + resource facts.
# The cost model is capability-BLIND; capability enters ONLY through the legality
# prune, so the SAME argmin diverges by capability -- a Zvl128b (full-V) target
# selects the strip-elided ggml-beating shape, a non-Zvl128b target has the
# elided shapes pruned and the same argmin selects the robust shape. Flipping
# ONLY the Zvl128b fact flips the shape (derived, not a constant). The vreg-budget
# prune binds when shrunk; the Zvl128b derivation is real ISA reasoning.

# CHECK: N3 Q4_0 cost model is capability-blind + measurement-calibrated (robust U-curve min@2, elided min@4, mf4 loses)
# CHECK: N3 Zvl128b target selects (m1, factor=4, elided) -- the ggml beat
# CHECK: N3 non-Zvl128b target prunes all elided shapes and selects (m1, factor=2, robust) -- the robust optimum
# CHECK: N3 flipping ONLY the Zvl128b fact flips strip_elision elided<->robust (derived, not a constant)
# CHECK: N3 vreg-budget prune binds: a 3-vreg budget prunes all (fail-closed); a 5-vreg budget prunes the wider m1 footprint
# CHECK: N3 Zvl128b derivation: rv64gcv=>true, zve32x/zve64x=>false, explicit zvl128b+/=>true (real ISA reasoning)
# CHECK: RVV N3 Q4_0 capability/resource-aware shape selection tests passed
